<section class="section">
    <div class="r-container">
        <div class="d-flex flex-lg-row flex-column-reverse gap-3">
            <div class="col col-lg-12">
                <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                    
                    <p>
                        Our Mental Health Care service supports individuals who are living with mental health challenges such as anxiety, depression, bipolar disorder, personality disorder, or psychosis. We provide respectful, person centred support that promotes stability, confidence, and improved wellbeing. Our team understands the importance of patience, encouragement, and compassionate care in helping people build their independence and manage their daily lives more effectively.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        We begin with an assessment to understand the individual’s needs, strengths, goals, and any specific challenges they may experience. This includes looking at daily routines, medication, communication preferences, emotional triggers, and the level of support required. Working in partnership with the person and, where appropriate, their family, we create a personalised plan that is supportive, flexible, and designed to enhance wellbeing.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Our carers provide assistance with daily living, including personal care, meals, medication reminders, and help with maintaining a structured routine. They also support individuals in accessing the community, attending appointments, and building confidence through social interaction. Encouragement and emotional support are central to our approach, helping individuals feel listened to, understood, and empowered.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Many people living with mental health conditions benefit from gentle support with tasks such as budgeting, organising the home, managing stress, or maintaining relationships. Our carers help individuals develop positive coping strategies and recognise early signs of change, ensuring that support is provided before difficulties escalate. With consent, we liaise with mental health teams, GPs, and other professionals to keep care consistent.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Families often appreciate the guidance and reassurance our service offers. Caring for someone with mental health needs can be emotionally demanding, and we provide information, updates, and encouragement where needed. By working closely with everyone involved, we help create a stable and supportive environment.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Our Mental Health Care service aims to promote independence, self confidence, and emotional wellbeing. Through understanding, consistency, and compassionate support, we help individuals feel more secure, hopeful, and in control of their lives.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
